context: Unlike all other <b5_0>British Government<b5_0/> records, the records from the East India Company (and its successor the India Office) are not in <a1_0><b4_0>The National Archives at Kew<a1_0/>, London<b4_0/>, but are held by the <a0_0><b3_0>British Library in London<b3_0/><a0_0/> as part of the Asia, Pacific and Africa Collections. <a2_0>The catalogue is searchable online in the Access to Archives catalogues<a2_0/>. <b6_0>Many of the East India Company records<b6_0/> are freely available online under an agreement that the Families in British India Society has with the British Library. Published catalogues exist of <b7_0>East India Company<b7_0/> ships' journals and logs, 1600–1834; and of some of the Company's daughter institutions, including the East India Company College, Haileybury, and Addiscombe Military Seminary.
